WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:04.656
I had him.

00:04.700 --> 00:06.441
I had him
dead to rights.

00:06.484 --> 00:09.966
But you didn't want him
dead to rights, HerrStarr.

00:10.010 --> 00:14.623
You wanted to make
him suffer. Yes?

00:16.538 --> 00:17.930
So,

00:19.062 --> 00:22.761
let's make
him suffer.

00:22.805 --> 00:25.416
I want to carve a vagina
onto his head.

00:25.460 --> 00:28.376
I think that falls
under the category
of suffering!

00:28.419 --> 00:29.986
[GOD LAUGHING]

00:30.421 --> 00:32.380
A vagina!

00:34.599 --> 00:36.993
All due respect,
My Lord,

00:37.907 --> 00:40.562
but what is it
that you want?

00:42.999 --> 00:44.174
Yeah...

00:46.350 --> 00:50.050
The great question
of the universe.

00:52.356 --> 00:54.967
Well, for one thing,
what I want

00:55.011 --> 00:57.274
is to know how
my Child is doing.

01:00.016 --> 01:04.542
Jesus is expected soon.
He's representing Heaven
at the conference...

01:04.586 --> 01:07.067
Not him, the other one.
The funny one.

01:07.980 --> 01:11.332
The one you call "Humperdoo."

01:12.376 --> 01:14.161
Oh! Yes.

01:15.771 --> 01:17.425
Well.

01:17.468 --> 01:20.515
That's a nickname.
A term of affection.

01:20.558 --> 01:21.646
How is he?

01:24.649 --> 01:26.564
Thriving under your care,
I trust.

01:27.652 --> 01:32.004
Good. I saw him
just this morning.

01:32.048 --> 01:34.094
High spirits, as always.

01:35.704 --> 01:36.879
Good.

01:40.274 --> 01:42.580
God, I love that kid.

01:42.624 --> 01:46.454
Yes, he's something else.

01:46.497 --> 01:50.545
He's integral, to all of it.

01:50.588 --> 01:51.633
To everything.

01:52.286 --> 01:53.809
Yes, of course.

01:56.464 --> 01:59.510
Do your part, Allfather,

01:59.554 --> 02:02.861
and you will earn
your long-lost reward.

02:04.820 --> 02:07.388
[HUMS MY WAY]

02:18.747 --> 02:21.141
Visage pristinus.

02:22.272 --> 02:24.666
Handsome and unsullied.

02:24.709 --> 02:27.190
That's what
you want, yes?

02:27.886 --> 02:29.410
Your looks back.

02:32.282 --> 02:33.762
[LAUGHS]

02:35.372 --> 02:38.680
We're going
to carve a vagina!

02:39.768 --> 02:42.249
Into Jesse Custer's soul.

02:47.210 --> 02:49.038
His soul?

02:50.431 --> 02:52.172
Have faith, Allfather.

02:53.869 --> 02:56.132
My great design is at work...

02:58.265 --> 03:00.484
And it's going
to be beautiful.

03:10.755 --> 03:12.279
[OVER PA SYSTEM]
This is your Captain Steve.[ALARMS BLARING]

03:12.322 --> 03:16.544
Looks like we've hit
a little patch of...
something.

03:16.587 --> 03:19.155
Please fasten your seat belts and try to remain calm.

03:19.199 --> 03:20.765
[WHOOPS]

03:20.809 --> 03:22.550
[EXCITED LAUGHTER]

03:22.593 --> 03:24.378
[GUFFAWS]

03:25.422 --> 03:27.163
[LOUD CRASH]

03:28.338 --> 03:30.035
[WATER SLOSHING]

03:38.522 --> 03:40.132
[GASPING FOR BREATH]

03:40.176 --> 03:41.525
[GRUNTS]

03:50.969 --> 03:52.232
[GASPS]

03:57.149 --> 03:58.368
Well, that was lucky.

04:04.244 --> 04:05.419
That the best you got?

04:11.903 --> 04:13.862
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

04:58.210 --> 04:59.473
CASSIDY: You know
what you look like to me,

04:59.516 --> 05:01.475
with your good bag
and your cheap shoes?

05:02.737 --> 05:04.129
You look like a rube.

05:04.956 --> 05:06.480
You're in a new mood.

05:06.523 --> 05:09.657
Oh, well,
nothing like a nice walk
to lift the spirits.

05:09.700 --> 05:10.962
Or a roll, if you will.

05:16.968 --> 05:19.362
Vampire coming up,
three minutes.

05:19.406 --> 05:21.495
Copy that.
Hold, please.

05:21.538 --> 05:24.019
What's this?
Emissary just arrived.

05:24.062 --> 05:25.716
No shit.
Which one?

05:25.760 --> 05:26.848
Heaven or Hell?

05:29.024 --> 05:30.373
FRANKIE: Oh, shit.

05:34.899 --> 05:36.118
Not Heaven.

05:37.380 --> 05:38.990
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

05:45.606 --> 05:49.044
Did you see...
Man, I should
have taken a picture!

05:49.087 --> 05:52.787
Whoo! Boy. Eh?
Goose pimples,
am I right?

05:52.830 --> 05:56.921
And, listen,
now that is true evil.

05:56.965 --> 05:59.968
Not some make-believe
Chianti-cannibal movie shrink

06:00.011 --> 06:03.319
who's supposed to be scary
'cause he can get into
your mind.

06:03.363 --> 06:05.930
Nah, old Adolf, when he wanted
to get in your mind,

06:05.974 --> 06:08.716
he just cracked your skull
open and took it. Am I right?

06:13.373 --> 06:15.070
What's this shit now?

06:24.166 --> 06:25.341
Yo!

06:29.867 --> 06:31.434
Hey.

06:31.478 --> 06:33.305
Where they at?
Who?

06:33.349 --> 06:35.351
"Who?" You're funny.

06:35.395 --> 06:37.745
Where'd they go?
You mean the guard fellas?

06:38.615 --> 06:40.704
Yeah, I killed them.

06:40.748 --> 06:43.141
Did you now? With what,
your smart mouth?

06:43.185 --> 06:46.362
I picked the lock
with an angel feather,

06:46.406 --> 06:48.886
then I snapped their necks
before they had a chance
to scream.

06:49.974 --> 06:51.802
[CHUCKLES]

06:51.846 --> 06:53.500
Let me tell you,

06:53.543 --> 06:56.633
get your funny out now because
when we get to Bensonhurst,

06:56.677 --> 06:58.374
ain't nobody
gonna be laughing.

07:02.160 --> 07:04.075
Oh, shit!

07:04.119 --> 07:05.425
[FRANKIE GRUNTS]

07:10.560 --> 07:12.432
[BOTH GRUNTING]

07:16.131 --> 07:17.306
[FRANKIE GROANING]

07:24.835 --> 07:26.010
[PANTS]

07:43.332 --> 07:44.464
[FRANKIE SCREAMS]

07:47.771 --> 07:48.729
[GROANS]

07:55.300 --> 07:56.606
[CRACKS NECK]

07:57.651 --> 07:59.043
Where you going, Frankie?

07:59.870 --> 08:01.002
[GROANING]

08:02.525 --> 08:03.613
Go on.

08:08.096 --> 08:09.750
What are you doing?

08:09.793 --> 08:12.013
[RIPS PANTS]
No, come on, not like this!
Not like this!

08:12.056 --> 08:14.842
Not like this! No!

08:14.885 --> 08:16.191
No!

08:16.234 --> 08:18.106
No!

08:22.458 --> 08:23.851
[THUDS]
[SCREAMS AND SOBS]

08:24.982 --> 08:26.941
This ain't right.
This ain't right.

08:26.984 --> 08:28.943
Frankie. Frankie,
listen to me! Frank!

08:29.552 --> 08:30.727
Settle down.

08:30.771 --> 08:33.251
The lambs are about
to stop screaming.

08:33.600 --> 08:34.731
Huh?

08:34.775 --> 08:36.211
[GUNSHOT]

08:48.005 --> 08:49.790
[BEEPS]

08:49.833 --> 08:52.183
Sorry for the hold-up there,
gents. Vampire coming up
in three minutes.

08:52.967 --> 08:54.098
Ha. [KISSES]

09:03.064 --> 09:04.282
[THUNDERCLAP]

09:12.421 --> 09:15.032
Buddy, are we dead?

09:15.076 --> 09:17.208
We're not gonna die.
Trust me.

09:18.253 --> 09:19.559
Hitler was wrong.

09:21.343 --> 09:23.954
What?
Hitler was wrong.

09:23.998 --> 09:27.044
We just survived a plane crash
without a scratch!

09:27.088 --> 09:29.003
It's a miracle!

09:29.046 --> 09:31.701
You think now an itsy-bitsy
little bit of rain

09:31.745 --> 09:35.096
is gonna stop us? No siree!
We're lost at sea.

09:35.139 --> 09:40.101
Unregistered flight,
no transponders,
no instruments.

09:40.144 --> 09:43.495
Compared to
a West Texas thunderstorm,
this ain't nothing!

09:45.280 --> 09:46.934
We just gotta stay positive.

09:48.588 --> 09:49.937
[MOANS]

09:49.980 --> 09:51.112
What's the point?

09:51.155 --> 09:52.592
We're just gonna
die anyway.

09:57.205 --> 09:59.990
We're gonna get to Australia
one way or another.

10:00.034 --> 10:02.166
So cut your whining!

10:04.212 --> 10:05.561
[IN WORD OF GOD]
And be positive!

10:08.651 --> 10:10.044
You're right!

10:10.087 --> 10:12.612
Then what the heck
are we gabbing here for, huh?

10:12.655 --> 10:13.787
Let's bail!

10:19.357 --> 10:22.534
You're just gonna sit there
shampooing your hair?

10:22.578 --> 10:24.624
Or are you gonna
toss some water?

10:24.667 --> 10:25.886
[BOTH LAUGH]

10:31.326 --> 10:32.457
CASSIDY: Christ.

10:36.723 --> 10:38.550
[WHISTLING]

10:45.035 --> 10:46.123
[GASPS]

10:46.167 --> 10:48.517
[GUN COCKS]
[CLEARS THROAT]

10:48.560 --> 10:51.085
Where is she?
"She" who?

10:51.999 --> 10:54.088
You know who. Tulip.

10:55.176 --> 10:57.134
I've known a few Tulips
in my time.

10:57.178 --> 10:59.571
And a handful of Daisys.
And a single Rose.

11:01.399 --> 11:03.097
Which Tulip might
you be looking for?

11:04.533 --> 11:06.187
The stupid one.

11:06.230 --> 11:08.537
She blew off her boyfriend
and came back here,

11:08.580 --> 11:11.627
I'm betting for
no good reason than
to save your bony ass.

11:11.671 --> 11:12.933
Why would she do that?

11:14.064 --> 11:15.413
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

11:18.199 --> 11:21.376
FEATHERSTONE: Like I said,
she's really stupid.

11:21.419 --> 11:23.813
You're right.
She's super stupid.

11:28.122 --> 11:29.427
But I haven't seen her.

11:33.823 --> 11:36.521
You, mop up Frankie.

11:36.565 --> 11:39.176
The rest of you,
let's get him
back downstairs.

11:48.925 --> 11:50.710
[INDISTINCT MESSAGE OVER PA]

11:52.624 --> 11:53.756
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

11:53.800 --> 11:54.931
HOOVER TWO: You.

11:58.500 --> 11:59.631
Come with me.

12:08.989 --> 12:10.686
FEATHERSTONE:
Make sure those are tight.

12:10.730 --> 12:12.470
Don't want our bait
wriggling off the hook.

12:12.514 --> 12:15.560
You call this tight?
I can still
feel me fingers, boys.

12:17.954 --> 12:18.912
Not for long.

12:22.437 --> 12:23.699
[GROANS]

12:37.757 --> 12:39.106
Now we wait.

12:41.761 --> 12:44.198
So, how was Bensonhurst?

12:46.766 --> 12:48.724
I can't believe
she came back
for me.

12:48.768 --> 12:50.291
Oh, that's wonderful.

12:51.553 --> 12:53.163
Wait, who?

12:53.207 --> 12:54.948
Tulip.
Ah, blessed girl.

12:55.644 --> 12:56.819
Never doubted her.

12:57.820 --> 12:59.343
Of course, she came back.

12:59.387 --> 13:00.388
[SIGHS]

13:04.218 --> 13:06.742
She's gonna keep coming back.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.135
What's the problem
with that?

13:11.442 --> 13:13.618
The Emissary requires
a personal valet.

13:13.662 --> 13:14.794
TULIP: Mmm-hmm.

13:14.837 --> 13:16.621
And you do not
look him in the eye.

13:16.665 --> 13:18.493
Do not speak to him
unless spoken to.

13:18.536 --> 13:20.451
No selfies.
No autographs.

13:23.715 --> 13:25.587
Sir.

13:25.630 --> 13:30.461
I just remembered,
I have a ton of work to do
down in the prison area,

13:30.505 --> 13:33.900
and my supervisor's probably
freaking out as we speak.

13:33.943 --> 13:39.862
How about I go down there
and sort all that out,
and then come back

13:41.995 --> 13:46.086
to the Emissary suite,
which sounds cool,
by the way,

13:46.129 --> 13:48.871
I just don't wanna
abandon my duties, sir.

13:51.134 --> 13:53.223
So, what do you think?

13:53.267 --> 13:56.400
I think that
for over 1,900 years,

13:56.444 --> 13:59.795
Grail disciples have
sacrificed, preparing
themselves for the rewards

13:59.839 --> 14:03.712
that will be brought forth
by this summit between
Heaven and Hell.

14:03.755 --> 14:06.584
And by the man
in this room.

14:06.628 --> 14:11.067
For anyone to refuse the honor
of playing even the smallest
part in its apotheosis

14:11.111 --> 14:15.985
would be so incomprehensible
to me that I could only
explain it as treasonous.

14:17.465 --> 14:18.640
Right.

14:25.647 --> 14:26.648
Hmm.

14:27.431 --> 14:28.998
Nice.

14:29.042 --> 14:30.826
Don't talk.

14:30.870 --> 14:35.483
Don't speak, no selfies,
and don't touch.

14:35.526 --> 14:37.137
Yeah, you said that.

14:37.180 --> 14:41.881
But if he touches you,
you should respond...
Positively.

15:04.904 --> 15:05.905
[INAUDIBLE]

15:18.918 --> 15:19.962
[DOOR CREAKS]
MAN: Hey.

15:30.930 --> 15:32.018
Jesus.

15:35.847 --> 15:36.892
[PANTING]

15:46.728 --> 15:47.859
[STRAINING]

15:50.123 --> 15:51.428
It's not the doing,

15:51.472 --> 15:53.169
it's the trying,
I always say.

15:53.213 --> 15:55.084
Shut your hole, Birdman!

15:55.128 --> 15:57.217
Christ.
To be free as a bird.

15:57.260 --> 16:00.655
To roost and preen and hunt!

16:00.698 --> 16:06.182
Love bound to hatchlings
as I return again and again

16:06.226 --> 16:09.185
with regurgitated
insect scraps.

16:09.229 --> 16:12.754
Shut your hole! For like
a minute. I dare you.

16:12.797 --> 16:14.060
That's not a problem.

16:17.019 --> 16:17.977
[SIGHS]

16:22.938 --> 16:24.374
How long was that?

16:27.203 --> 16:29.510
It was like six seconds.
That felt like forever.

16:29.553 --> 16:30.772
[GROANS]

16:30.815 --> 16:32.295
Where's your girlfriend?
She coming?

16:32.339 --> 16:34.167
She's not my girlfriend.
Yeah, right!

16:34.210 --> 16:35.690
She isn't!

16:35.733 --> 16:37.648
[IN CASSIDY'S VOICE]
I can't believe
she came back for me.

16:37.692 --> 16:39.911
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
You almost goobered
into your galoshes...

16:39.955 --> 16:41.522
It's my mate's girlfriend!

16:42.697 --> 16:44.699
Forbidden love? The best.

16:44.742 --> 16:47.702
Look, it's not love,
you bastard! All right?

16:47.745 --> 16:50.748
It's her pigheadedness.
They've got me.
She doesn't like it.

16:50.792 --> 16:54.535
So she's coming to get me.
And that's it.
And they know it!

16:54.578 --> 16:55.753
They know she's coming.

16:58.321 --> 16:59.540
And when she does...

17:03.065 --> 17:04.414
They're going to kill her.

17:06.677 --> 17:09.724
That's a grievous
turn of events.

17:09.767 --> 17:13.945
Your forbidden love wandering
into a trap like a mouse
to the cheese.

17:13.989 --> 17:16.774
A trap you're responsible
for setting,

17:16.818 --> 17:17.993
if we're being honest.

17:20.474 --> 17:23.172
[SIGHS] What to do?
What to do?

17:23.216 --> 17:27.176
I'll tell you
what I'm gonna do.
I'm gonna break out of these.

17:27.220 --> 17:28.743
And then, I'm gonna kill you.

17:30.353 --> 17:31.354
Huh.

17:31.746 --> 17:33.052
Yeah.

17:33.095 --> 17:34.357
[WAVES LAPPING]

17:34.401 --> 17:36.229
STEVE: Would you look
at that sun?

17:38.883 --> 17:40.755
Ninety-three million
miles away,

17:41.930 --> 17:43.671
and you can still feel it.

17:43.714 --> 17:46.239
Yeah, that's gonna work.

17:46.282 --> 17:51.244
Whoo, boy. It's a good thing
you told me
not to bring pants.

17:51.287 --> 17:53.376
My legs can really
feel it now.

17:55.161 --> 17:56.249
Jesus.

17:58.033 --> 17:59.382
Where's that
first-aid kit?

17:59.426 --> 18:01.254
Yeah, first-aid
would be great.

18:01.297 --> 18:06.172
Like an aspirin or a shot
of morphine. Or even
a bone saw would be welcome.

18:06.215 --> 18:07.434
Or you know what we can do?
We can catch some fish

18:07.477 --> 18:10.437
and just fry them up
on my legs thighs.

18:10.480 --> 18:13.527
Let me think.
You know what?
That's a good idea.

18:13.570 --> 18:16.617
Now, thinking is like
the answer to everything.

18:16.660 --> 18:18.619
Can you be quiet?
Good idea.

18:18.662 --> 18:23.189
Yeah. Let's just
take in the silence.

18:25.408 --> 18:27.018
The sweet serenity
of the sea.

18:27.062 --> 18:28.324
[IN WORD OF GOD]
Stop being positive!

18:29.499 --> 18:31.849
[YELLING] Oh, my God!

18:32.415 --> 18:35.114
Holy son of a...

18:35.157 --> 18:36.463
[IN WORD OF GOD]
Feel no pain!

18:42.817 --> 18:44.297
That's so cool.

18:48.562 --> 18:49.563
[GRUNTS]

18:54.481 --> 18:57.266
We're maybe gonna
die out here, huh?

18:58.702 --> 19:00.051
No, we're not gonna die.

19:02.141 --> 19:03.229
Listen to me.

19:05.579 --> 19:06.754
What is your name?

19:09.104 --> 19:10.323
Steve.
Steve.

19:12.890 --> 19:14.196
All right, Steve, look.

19:16.503 --> 19:19.549
This whole thing,
your legs,
the plane crash,

19:19.593 --> 19:21.116
it's all just a test
from God.

19:23.640 --> 19:25.076
Like the prophets of old.

19:26.730 --> 19:28.428
He doesn't want
to kill us.

19:30.995 --> 19:32.910
He just wants to see
what we're made of.

19:34.434 --> 19:36.175
And we're gonna
show him, okay?

19:38.351 --> 19:40.004
But what if I don't
believe in God?

19:42.355 --> 19:44.008
I wouldn't blame
you for that.

19:47.142 --> 19:48.883
You don't need
to believe in Him.

19:51.277 --> 19:52.452
Just believe in me.

19:55.672 --> 19:57.761
[CHUCKLES]
Okay.

20:00.982 --> 20:03.463
I mean, you got us
this far, right?

20:03.506 --> 20:06.422
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

20:19.218 --> 20:20.697
You're to be my valet.

20:21.394 --> 20:22.351
Yeah, uh...

20:24.484 --> 20:29.097
Thing is, I don't really
know a whole lot about,
um, valeting.

20:29.140 --> 20:34.450
But he said they're
short-staffed... We're
short-staffed. The Grail is.

20:34.494 --> 20:37.888
Yeah, and I'm to be it.
I will be valeting you.

20:41.414 --> 20:42.458
What's your name?

20:43.242 --> 20:44.721
Marnie Pomerantz.

20:46.680 --> 20:47.855
I'm Jesus Christ.

20:54.383 --> 20:57.038
What?
Marnie, you're in trouble.

20:58.387 --> 20:59.606
[KNOCK AT DOOR]

21:07.178 --> 21:09.485
Do you mind?
Oh. Yeah.

21:19.321 --> 21:20.627
JESUS: Allfather.

21:21.149 --> 21:22.281
Your Grace.

21:26.110 --> 21:29.200
Masada is at your disposal.

21:29.244 --> 21:34.293
Food court, gym, steam, sauna.
There's a chapel... Somewhere.

21:35.555 --> 21:39.515
Your counterpart from Hell
has also just arrived.

21:39.559 --> 21:41.038
I imagine...
Allfather.

21:42.170 --> 21:45.216
Your ear,
it looks like...

21:45.260 --> 21:48.437
Nothing to concern
yourself about.

21:48.481 --> 21:51.048
A surgeon assures me
it's on the mend.

21:51.527 --> 21:52.833
Ah.

21:52.876 --> 21:54.487
Well. [CLEARS THROAT]

21:54.530 --> 21:56.315
If there's nothing else...

21:56.358 --> 21:59.579
You're a most
gracious host, Allfather.

22:11.199 --> 22:12.331
Do I know you?

22:13.680 --> 22:15.334
No, sir.

22:15.377 --> 22:17.901
Your face
is familiar.

22:17.945 --> 22:19.816
TULIP: Uh...

22:19.860 --> 22:22.166
Maybe you've seen me
in the food court.

22:22.732 --> 22:25.648
No. I know you.

22:28.434 --> 22:29.478
Allfather.

22:31.306 --> 22:34.135
When do I get
to meet my Child?

22:34.178 --> 22:37.878
My descendant.
Flesh of my flesh.

22:38.531 --> 22:40.402
I hear...

22:40.446 --> 22:42.796
He's quite a dancer.
Ah, indeed.

22:44.319 --> 22:46.103
Fear not, Your Grace.

22:46.147 --> 22:51.457
When the time is right,
I am certain you'll have
a glorious introduction.

22:53.110 --> 22:54.634
Until then, Your Grace.

23:01.292 --> 23:04.383
See? You are in trouble.

23:24.272 --> 23:26.143
[BEEPS]

23:29.451 --> 23:30.409
[WHIRRING]

23:34.935 --> 23:36.632
[BLOWS]

23:36.676 --> 23:39.330
Jesus is asking
after his Child.

23:39.809 --> 23:41.202
Oh.

23:41.245 --> 23:43.422
How are we progressing
with the clone replacement?

23:43.465 --> 23:45.946
Of course, we don't even
have an airdate yet,

23:45.989 --> 23:48.992
but, would he
be presentable?

23:50.559 --> 23:51.778
[SIGHS]

23:51.821 --> 23:54.824
No one can know we lost him.
Understand? No one.

23:54.868 --> 23:57.871
Of course. I'll make sure
the replacement is ready
if need be.

24:04.225 --> 24:05.226
Hmm.

24:09.970 --> 24:12.625
Something else
on your mind, sir?No.

24:15.628 --> 24:17.325
Permission to speak
freely, sir?

24:23.331 --> 24:25.159
I can't help
but notice a certain

24:26.247 --> 24:29.990
languidness in you,
as of late, sir.

24:30.033 --> 24:34.124
As your sworn confidant,
I'd be remiss in my duties
to not remind you that...

24:35.169 --> 24:37.258
Despite these recent setbacks,

24:37.301 --> 24:40.566
you are still the sole
and sovereign Allfather.

24:40.609 --> 24:43.090
The full force of the Grail
at your disposal.

24:43.133 --> 24:45.919
The world
at your fingertips.

24:45.962 --> 24:49.313
And from where I stand,
while things may seem
at their darkest,

24:49.357 --> 24:51.794
in my humble opinion,
you are, in fact,

24:52.795 --> 24:54.057
sitting pretty.

24:58.801 --> 25:01.978
Presentation packet
on your desk, sir.
I'll leave you to it.

25:07.854 --> 25:08.811
[DOOR OPENS]

25:10.596 --> 25:11.597
[DOOR CLOSES]

25:12.946 --> 25:15.731
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

25:17.777 --> 25:18.778
Hmm.

25:21.432 --> 25:23.391
"Sitting pretty."

25:25.654 --> 25:26.873
[WET PLOP]

25:47.850 --> 25:49.548
Make sure
you tie off the knot.

25:53.464 --> 25:55.858
[CHUCKLES] And then...

25:58.252 --> 26:02.212
Make the back stay tight.

26:03.910 --> 26:04.911
Huh.

26:09.655 --> 26:11.352
All we need now
is some wind.

26:19.403 --> 26:21.101
[WIND BLOWS]

26:23.494 --> 26:24.626
[VICTORIOUS LAUGH]

26:36.072 --> 26:38.771
Where the hell did you learn
how to do that?

26:38.814 --> 26:41.643
A girl I know. She's good
at this kind of thing.

26:41.687 --> 26:43.906
Damn.
Oh, this is nothing.

26:45.821 --> 26:49.912
I once saw her build
a land mine out of lawnmower
and root beer. [CHUCKLES]

26:49.956 --> 26:51.610
STEVE: Yeah?

26:51.653 --> 26:54.134
All I need is a woman
who knows how to iron
a dress shirt...

26:54.177 --> 26:55.483
Shit, your arm!

26:58.094 --> 26:59.487
My... My hand.

26:59.530 --> 27:01.794
It was dangling
in the water.
A shark must have...

27:01.837 --> 27:03.012
How did I not feel it?

27:04.492 --> 27:06.015
'Cause I told you not to.

27:07.538 --> 27:08.583
[GRUNTS]

27:08.627 --> 27:10.193
That's better.

27:10.237 --> 27:11.891
But it looks like
it's really hurt.

27:12.935 --> 27:16.069
Hey. Here's the plan.

27:16.112 --> 27:18.549
We're gonna sail
to that beach
in Australia.

27:18.593 --> 27:20.769
We're gonna get a bunch
of beers, a couple
of nice steaks,

27:20.813 --> 27:23.250
we're gonna sit in the sun
and we're gonna
get you fixed up.

27:23.293 --> 27:24.468
That is the plan, right?

27:28.559 --> 27:29.778
[WHOOSHING]

27:33.826 --> 27:35.175
Oh, you son of a bitch!

27:36.089 --> 27:37.786
I see what you're doing.

27:37.830 --> 27:41.094
This is between me and you.
Not him!

27:41.137 --> 27:43.618
He's gonna die out here,
unless you cut this shit,

27:43.662 --> 27:45.794
and do something right now!

27:52.758 --> 27:53.889
What'd he say?

28:02.028 --> 28:03.377
He said "soon."

28:04.726 --> 28:05.684
Oh, good.

28:09.557 --> 28:11.690
Sooner's probably
better than later.

28:17.130 --> 28:18.697
Sorry I lied before.

28:20.133 --> 28:22.178
You seem like
a super nice person.

28:23.092 --> 28:24.093
Obviously.

28:25.747 --> 28:29.229
You seem like
a nice person too, Marnie.

28:32.667 --> 28:35.801
Actually, my name's Tulip.
I lied about that too,
I'm sorry.

28:39.500 --> 28:40.588
I see.

28:40.631 --> 28:41.632
Look...

28:43.504 --> 28:48.291
I didn't mean to get you
involved in all my sh...
My stuff.

28:49.728 --> 28:52.252
So I don't know.
I'm just gonna
get out of here.

28:54.863 --> 28:55.908
To your friend?

28:57.257 --> 28:58.432
Uh-huh.

28:58.475 --> 28:59.694
The one who's in trouble.

29:00.390 --> 29:01.696
Maybe I can help you.

29:02.697 --> 29:04.873
Oh, wow.

29:04.917 --> 29:07.571
That's like really
cool of you,
Jesus, but...

29:07.615 --> 29:09.051
What is it,
my child?

29:11.227 --> 29:12.838
You don't think
that I can help?

29:12.881 --> 29:14.448
[CHUCKLES]

29:14.491 --> 29:17.407
This isn't a
"turn the other cheek"
kind of thing.

29:18.234 --> 29:21.847
Okay? This is a jailbreak.

29:21.890 --> 29:24.763
Things are gonna get ugly.
They're gonna get violent.

29:25.981 --> 29:27.374
Possibly, deadly.

29:28.941 --> 29:32.074
Oh, my.
Yeah.

29:32.118 --> 29:35.643
So, no, I don't think
you can help.

29:39.255 --> 29:40.300
We'll see.

29:51.050 --> 29:52.399
GUARD 1: [WHISPERING]
I need to go to the bathroom.

29:53.313 --> 29:54.836
[OTHER GUARDS SHUSHING]

29:56.882 --> 29:58.797
GUARD 1: I'm sorry,
I really need to go.

29:58.840 --> 30:00.276
[SHUSHING CONTINUES]

30:00.320 --> 30:01.277
GUARD 2: [WHISPERING]
Chill. She will kill you.

30:05.194 --> 30:07.370
GUARD 1: If I knew we were
gonna be here this long...

30:07.414 --> 30:09.503
[STABS]
[GROANS]

30:11.331 --> 30:12.332
[THUDDING]

30:16.727 --> 30:19.208
GUARD 1: Okay,
I went in my pants.

30:19.252 --> 30:20.340
[SHUSHES]

30:22.995 --> 30:24.387
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

30:34.223 --> 30:35.268
FEATHERSTONE: Jesus.

30:36.182 --> 30:37.357
GUARDS: Jesus.

30:39.054 --> 30:41.100
What a pleasant surprise.
Can we help you?

30:41.143 --> 30:43.102
I'm here to bless
the prisoners.

30:44.581 --> 30:47.410
"Prisoners"?
This is the dungeon, yes?

30:48.237 --> 30:49.717
You must have prisoners.

30:49.760 --> 30:53.329
This is a dungeon, My Lord.
Masada has many.

30:53.373 --> 30:55.201
In fact, there's one
in the north wing.

30:55.244 --> 30:57.377
Mormons and pederasts.
They'll be thrilled.

30:57.420 --> 30:58.682
I'll have someone
show you the way.

31:00.597 --> 31:02.861
I want to bless
the prisoners here.

31:02.904 --> 31:06.908
This is just a training area.

31:08.214 --> 31:10.172
There are no
prisoners here.

31:10.216 --> 31:11.913
CASSIDY:
I said, "Shut up."

31:14.960 --> 31:17.440
I'm sorry.
I can't let you in.

31:17.484 --> 31:20.661
You can do anything
you want, my child.

31:20.704 --> 31:24.273
Scale mountains,
cross oceans,

31:24.317 --> 31:26.101
crawl through the eye
of a needle.

31:27.015 --> 31:28.408
You can live forever.

31:29.713 --> 31:32.586
All you have to do,
is make way for me.

31:32.629 --> 31:33.804
Jesus.

31:35.589 --> 31:36.938
It's not gonna happen.

31:42.074 --> 31:43.075
What?

31:43.989 --> 31:44.990
It didn't work.

31:51.953 --> 31:53.041
[STRAINING]

31:57.828 --> 31:58.960
There you go.

32:00.614 --> 32:01.615
[GROANING IN PAIN]

32:06.228 --> 32:07.577
Pop goes the weasel.

32:12.321 --> 32:13.322
[GRUNTS]

32:16.412 --> 32:17.370
[SCREAMING IN PAIN]

32:25.769 --> 32:26.770
[PANTING]

32:31.297 --> 32:32.298
[WOOSHING]

32:40.567 --> 32:42.482
You could have
just untied me.

32:43.700 --> 32:44.701
[CASSIDY YELLS]

32:48.314 --> 32:52.274
Lung cancer,
heart disease.

32:52.318 --> 32:55.974
Being stabbed to death
as I sleep by
an angry ex-wife.

32:57.453 --> 32:58.977
That's how I thought I'd...

33:03.068 --> 33:04.504
But not in a raft.

33:05.896 --> 33:08.334
With no hand
and no pants.

33:10.510 --> 33:13.034
I came out
of a blackout once
with no pants on.

33:14.688 --> 33:16.516
Being chased by
the Rodriguez brothers.

33:17.996 --> 33:20.999
I promise you,
I'd take this
situation every day.

33:23.958 --> 33:26.308
I should have had
more sex with strangers.

33:26.352 --> 33:27.831
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

33:28.919 --> 33:31.052
I mean, I had sex
with a lot, but...

33:31.835 --> 33:33.228
I should have had more.

33:33.272 --> 33:35.100
[CHUCKLES]

33:36.057 --> 33:37.711
[COUGHS]

33:44.457 --> 33:46.546
I think I'm ready
for this test
to be over.

33:46.937 --> 33:48.113
SOON.

33:48.983 --> 33:50.071
I'm ready.

33:51.812 --> 33:53.901
I've done a lot
of bad things in my life.

33:55.903 --> 33:57.644
I've been
mean and selfish.

34:01.343 --> 34:03.041
I've been
married four times.

34:05.304 --> 34:07.262
And three times
for the money.

34:09.482 --> 34:10.918
But I'm done
with all of that.

34:14.095 --> 34:15.227
I believe in you now.

34:16.793 --> 34:18.795
Save me, God.

34:20.928 --> 34:22.712
Use your superpower
and save me.

34:24.279 --> 34:25.541
I'm not God.

34:25.585 --> 34:27.413
But I saw
what you can do.

34:27.456 --> 34:29.328
Genesis does not
work like that.

34:29.371 --> 34:31.112
Use the power
and save me.

34:31.156 --> 34:32.896
Save me, God!

34:32.940 --> 34:34.724
You promised
I wouldn't die!

34:34.768 --> 34:36.248
Please save me!

34:36.726 --> 34:37.901
[COUGHING]

34:39.686 --> 34:41.079
Do not die!

34:43.124 --> 34:44.256
[IN WORD OF GOD] Live!

34:44.821 --> 34:45.909
Live!

34:52.002 --> 34:53.743
[GASPING]

34:53.787 --> 34:54.831
Oh, God.

34:55.919 --> 34:57.095
Oh, God.

34:57.138 --> 34:58.226
The power.

35:01.534 --> 35:02.535
[COUGHS FRANTICALLY]

35:08.149 --> 35:10.064
You... You lied.

35:30.389 --> 35:32.173
Jesus.
It's a trap.

35:32.217 --> 35:35.568
There are soldiers with guns,
and they're waiting for you.

35:36.873 --> 35:38.092
Waiting's over.

35:42.749 --> 35:45.186
My child, this is madness.

35:52.411 --> 35:55.805
Please. Let's find
another way.

35:55.849 --> 35:57.329
I don't know any other way.

36:00.897 --> 36:02.072
Worship me.

36:04.074 --> 36:05.075
What?

36:06.599 --> 36:07.730
Kneel.

36:12.822 --> 36:14.476
GUARD: Jesus.

36:14.520 --> 36:16.348
Come on! What's the holdup?

36:17.349 --> 36:18.915
Excuse us, Your Grace.

36:18.959 --> 36:20.439
Some of us have jobs.

36:21.266 --> 36:22.832
On your feet, let's go!

36:31.885 --> 36:33.843
Hey, what happened?

36:33.887 --> 36:35.410
Prisoner. He's gone.

36:43.026 --> 36:44.506
JESUS: What do you think
happened here?

36:46.116 --> 36:47.553
He got himself out.

36:50.033 --> 36:52.122
So, what do you do now?

36:54.212 --> 36:57.040
Get out of here
and go find Cass.

36:57.084 --> 36:59.173
He's probably half-wasted
somewhere already.

36:59.217 --> 37:00.305
Then what?

37:04.091 --> 37:05.223
Then...

37:13.100 --> 37:14.493
Whatever the hell I want.

37:16.886 --> 37:18.018
Can I come?

37:46.525 --> 37:51.660
"When the perishable
must clothe itself
with the imperishable,

37:51.704 --> 37:54.707
"and the mortal
with immortality,

37:56.535 --> 37:59.233
"then the saying that was
written comes true.

37:59.277 --> 38:02.236
"'Death has been
swallowed up in victory.

38:03.672 --> 38:05.370
"'Where, O Death,
is your victory?

38:06.501 --> 38:08.677
"'Where, O Death,
is your sting?'"

38:09.809 --> 38:11.027
[WATER SPLASHING]

38:22.735 --> 38:25.390
You know what?
You're an asshole.

38:30.917 --> 38:32.005
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

38:51.633 --> 38:53.418
GUARD: I could get in
real trouble here, sir.

38:57.944 --> 38:58.945
Luger.

39:00.425 --> 39:02.035
Okay, you've got
five minutes.

39:22.055 --> 39:23.404
[WHIMPERING]

39:29.367 --> 39:30.759
Meing ott.

39:32.631 --> 39:34.154
Look at you.

39:43.337 --> 39:45.600
They say you have
a talent, My Lord.

39:47.820 --> 39:50.431
But I would like to see it
for myself, ja?

39:57.830 --> 39:59.005
Now...

40:00.833 --> 40:02.008
[CRACKS FINGERS]

40:03.575 --> 40:07.274
Let's start
with a bouncy one,
shall we?

40:07.753 --> 40:08.754
Ja.

40:10.320 --> 40:14.673
Eins, zwei, eins, zwei, drei, vier.[PLAYS PIANO]

40:29.905 --> 40:30.950
[MUMBLING]

40:30.993 --> 40:33.039
Australia, huh?

40:37.870 --> 40:39.132
You can hear him?

40:44.964 --> 40:46.052
Okay.

40:48.228 --> 40:49.229
So...

40:52.362 --> 40:54.321
How do we get there?

40:55.540 --> 40:56.845
[COCKS]

40:58.368 --> 40:59.848
[BLOWS]

41:22.828 --> 41:24.525
Crikey!

41:24.569 --> 41:27.441
Did you just crawl through
the center of the earth, mate?

41:27.485 --> 41:29.008
I would have thought
that was physically...

41:29.051 --> 41:30.313
[GUNSHOT]

42:00.561 --> 42:02.520
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
